  "ai_usage": "Use to choose better gradients and to teach color-space interpolation. Default CSS gradients interpolate in sRGB, which can pass through muddy grey between distant hues; add `in oklch` (perceptually uniform) for even, vivid transitions: `linear-gradient(in oklch, blue, yellow)`. Prefer oklch/oklab for brand gradients; provide an sRGB fallback for old browsers. Pick oklch for even lightness, hsl 'longer hue' for rainbows.",
  "path": "effects/color-systems/oklch-gradient.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>OKLCH vs sRGB Gradients</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"oklch-gradient\",\n    \"title\": \"OKLCH vs sRGB Gradients\",\n    \"summary\": \"The same two colors interpolated in sRGB versus OKLCH — OKLCH stays vivid and even, sRGB muddies through grey. A 2026 color-space upgrade.\",\n    \"description\": \"CSS now lets you choose the gradient interpolation color space. This side-by-side shows why OKLCH (perceptually uniform) beats the default sRGB: no dead grey midpoints, even lightness, punchier results — using `linear-gradient(in oklch, …)`.\",\n    \"theme\": \"color-systems\",\n    \"categories\": [\"color\", \"gradient\", \"css\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"oklch\", \"color-space\", \"gradient\", \"interpolation\", \"perceptual\", \"2026-trend\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"beginner\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"Interpolation hints (in oklch) in all current browsers; falls back to sRGB where unsupported.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"Static gradients — zero runtime cost.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Educational/decorative. Labels describe each bar so the comparison isn't color-only.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"stops\", \"description\": \"The two endpoint colors\", \"default\": \"blue → yellow\" },\n      { \"name\": \"space\", \"description\": \"oklch / oklab / hsl / srgb\", \"default\": \"oklch vs srgb\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Compare oklch vs hsl\", \"Three-stop gradients\", \"Use longer/shorter hue paths\"],\n    \"related\": [\"gradient-library\", \"animated-gradient\", \"semantic-color-tokens\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use to choose better gradients and to teach color-space interpolation. Default CSS gradients interpolate in sRGB, which can pass through muddy grey between distant hues; add `in oklch` (perceptually uniform) for even, vivid transitions: `linear-gradient(in oklch, blue, yellow)`. Prefer oklch/oklab for brand gradients; provide an sRGB fallback for old browsers. Pick oklch for even lightness, hsl 'longer hue' for rainbows.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root{--a:#1b4dff;--b:#ffd400;}\n    html,body{height:100%;margin:0}\n    body{display:grid;place-items:center;background:#0b0d12;color:#e8ecf6;font-family:system-ui,sans-serif;padding:2rem}\n    .panel{width:min(560px,92vw)}\n    h1{font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:800;margin:0 0 .3rem;text-align:center}\n    .sub{color:#8b93a7;text-align:center;margin:0 0 1.6rem;font-size:.95rem}\n    .row{margin-bottom:1.2rem}\n    .row .label{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:.8rem;color:#8b93a7;margin-bottom:.4rem;font-family:ui-monospace,monospace}\n    .bar{height:64px;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid #242a3b}\n    .srgb{background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--a),var(--b))}\n    .oklch{background:linear-gradient(90deg in oklch,var(--a),var(--b))}\n    .swatches{display:flex;gap:.5rem;justify-content:center;margin-top:.5rem}\n    .sw{width:28px;height:28px;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #242a3b}\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"panel\">\n    <h1>Gradient interpolation: sRGB vs OKLCH</h1>\n    <p class=\"sub\">Same two colors. Notice the muddy middle on top, the vivid even blend below.</p>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"label\"><span>linear-gradient(90deg, …)</span><span>sRGB (default)</span></div>\n      <div class=\"bar srgb\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"label\"><span>linear-gradient(90deg in oklch, …)</span><span>OKLCH ✓</span></div>\n      <div class=\"bar oklch\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"swatches\"><span class=\"sw\" style=\"background:var(--a)\"></span><span class=\"sw\" style=\"background:var(--b)\"></span></div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
